## Frontend changes needed

### services/api.js — no changes required
The API contract (endpoints, request shape) is backward-compatible.
`objective` now accepts the new values; old QSW params (omega, evolution_time)
can be ignored server-side.

### EnhancedQuantumDashboard.js
1. Update the objective dropdown to show new values:
   - equal_weight, markowitz, min_variance, hrp, qubo_sa, vqe, hybrid, target_return
2. Remove: omega slider, evolution_time slider, evolution_method dropdown
3. Add (optional): K_screen / K_select inputs for hybrid, shown only when objective=hybrid
4. Add: lambda_risk and gamma inputs for qubo_sa/hybrid (advanced section)

### simulationEngine.js
The simulation mode uses the JS QSW approximation. For MVP, leave simulation
mode as-is — it's acceptable for demos. When in LIVE mode the real backend
methods are used. A future task would be to write JS approximations of the
notebook methods for offline simulation.

